post_text:
BOCES classes will begin on Tuesday, September 8, 2020.

AM BOCES Students:

Bus students attending AM BOCES will be picked up in the morning with the elementary students. When arriving at LCS they will board the BOCES bus with vocational students who walk or drive to school.

These students will return to LCS at approximately 11:30 am. During remote learning, the BOCES bus students will be transported home.

PM BOCES Students:

PM Students will be picked up at their homes between 10:00-11:15. When arriving at LCS they will board the BOCES bus with vocational students who walk or drive to school.

These students will return to LCS approximately 3:00 pm. The BOCES bus students will then be transported home.

post_text:
DIGITAL YEARBOOK SIGNING SAVES THE DAY!
It’s been a spring like no other. Lots of special traditions have been cancelled — but not this one. Yearbook signing lives on.
Funny messages. Sweet scribbles. Heartfelt notes. All of the typical yearbook signing customs get to live on for the rest of time. And they’re all just a click away. Get signing today.

https://yearbooksigning.jostens.com/home

Use the link above to have friends sign your yearbook, then print out the pages to slide into your book when they arrive. The current ship date for our yearbooks is July 23rd. I will make sure books are distributed as soon as they arrive.

Historic Town of Lyme, New York added 30 new photos to the album: Lyme Central Class of 2020.
June 9 at 6:32 PM ·

Lyme Central and the Town hung up banners in the village of Chaumont to honor this year's senior class. The banners were coordinated by Heather DaSilva. The contributors who helped pay for the banners were Dr. Robert Early, Fred's Quick Lube, Linda Carney, Eleanor VanNess, the Parker family, Breanna Daggett, the Dowe family, The Duck Out, Christina Calhoun, Darla Taylor, Kristin Ward, Ted Smith, Jennifer Anne, Karen Green, Karina Aubertine, and Joe and Cora Marich. Some of the banners are obscured by trees or blowing in the wind...so the image doesn't reflect the beauty of the student.

post_text:
Meal delivery will begin Friday, March 20th for families who have requested this service . The schedule for meal deliveries after this Friday will be on Mondays, Wednesdays and Fridays. On Mondays and Wednesdays deliveries will include food for the following day.

We anticipate deliveries arriving at your home prior to 11 a.m. Please have a clearly marked crate, box, or tote at the end of your driveway by 8:00 a.m. for us to deliver your meals. For our families who have opted to pick up their meals at school, you may do so on Mondays, Wednesdays and Fridays beginning on March 20th between 9 and 10 a.m. at the Welcome Center. We thank you for your help and wish you well during this extended closure.

The Healthy Kids Program is looking for an assistant teacher or site supervisor to work at the after school program at Lyme. The program runs from 3PM until 6PM (at the latest).

Currently, there is an opening for someone to work from Monday to Wednesday. You will be paid for training and the position will begin as soon as possible. If you have a child(ren), they may be able to attend the program for free on the days you work at the program. Attached is a link describing the qualifications necessary for the positions. If you have any questions, please contact Sarah Purdy at spurdy@lymecsd.org.

post_text: On November 14th, fourteen juniors and three seniors were inducted into the Lyme Chapter of the National Honor Society, joining six returning members. This is one of the largest induction classes in the history of NHS at Lyme Central. All students in grades 6-12 were in attendance, and we were honored to have recent graduate Ms. Gabrielle Rickett return as our guest speaker. The four pillars of NHS - scholarship, character, leadership, and service - are exemplified by these students who are eager to serve their school and community. Pictured above - Back row: Wyatt Thomas, Camille Stevenson, Graham Rowland, Jacob Bombard, and Isaiah Wilson. Third row: Frederick O’Brien, Hailie Calhoun, Tyler Wilson, Marlana Wilson, Simarra Willett, and Riley Aubertine. Second row: Jaycee Paige, Logan Pettey, Olivia Ososkalo, Ashlyn Hilts, Aniyah Henderson, and Kimberleigh DaSilva. Front row: Vanessa Ashland, Breanna Bishop, Kimberly Finen, Damian Gessner, Molly Timmerman, and Trevor Weston.

post_text:
On Tuesday, November 26, 2019, Lyme Central School will practice an emergency go home drill from an alternative location- All Saints Catholic Church on Madison Street in Chaumont.

Busses will dismiss from All Saints at 2:45. You can anticipate your child arriving home between 15-20 minutes earlier than usual.

All walkers PreK-12 will be dismissed following the busses departure. Parents picking up their children are asked to park on Academy Street next to the school and walk to the church to pick up their students.

Students who have practice may return to the school following the drill.
